🧩 Problem: Merge Sorted Array

You are given two integer arrays nums1 and nums2, sorted in non-decreasing order, and two integers m and n.

nums1 has a size of m + n, where:
The first m elements are valid
The last n elements are 0s (placeholders) to hold elements from nums2

Merge nums2 into nums1 as one sorted array.

📥 Input
nums1: IntArray of size m + n
m: number of valid elements in nums1
nums2: IntArray of size n
n: number of elements in nums2

📤 Output
Do not return anything
Modify nums1 in-place

Example 1:
Input:
nums1 = [1,2,3,0,0,0], m = 3
nums2 = [2,5,6], n = 3

Output:
[1,2,2,3,5,6]


Solution:
class Solution {
    fun merge(nums1: IntArray, m: Int, nums2: IntArray, n: Int): Unit {
        var i = m-1 // valid elements in nums1
        var j = n-1 // valid elements in nums2
        var k = m+n-1 // index at which element will be added
        // we will start shifting elements from the back
        while(j>=0){
            // if nums1 ith element is larger shift nums1[i] to kth index
            if(i>=0 && nums1[i]>nums2[j]){
                nums1[k]=nums1[i]
                i--
            }
            // if nums1 ith element is smaller shift nums2[j] to kth index
            else{
                nums1[k] = nums2[j]
                j--
            }
             k--
        }
    }
}
